cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.LG, cs.CYBER, cs.CR 

This paper deals with predicting risk profiles of individuals in social networks, which involves analyzing social communities and their influence on individual behavior. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also involves machine learning techniques for prediction, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The analysis of social communities and their influence on behavior is also relevant to cs.SOC (Computational Social Science). The paper also deals with privacy concerns and the potential for individuals to withhold information, which could fall under cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
